MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: (let\s+\w+\s*=\s*Config\.|let\s+\w+\s*=\s*\w+\.(startSize|maxSize|timeLimitMs|silverBySize|maxLives|colorsCount|roundsPerGold))
ADVISORY: |
  `Config` in packages/shared-types/src/config.ts is `as const`, so every leaf
  literal value is pinned to its narrow literal type (e.g. `3`, `60_000`).

  If you assign one to a `let` that you then re-assign to a different value, TS
  will error: "Type '4' is not assignable to type '3'".

  WRONG:
      let currentSize = Config.game.recall.startSize; // type pins to literal `3`
      currentSize = 4;  // TS2322 error

  RIGHT — explicit type annotation:
      let currentSize: number = Config.game.recall.startSize;

  Or extract the value once and convert:
      const START_SIZE: number = Config.game.recall.startSize;
      let currentSize = START_SIZE;

  This ALSO hits `as const` arrays (silverBySize, prizePool) used as `readonly number[]` —
  indexing returns `number | undefined`, so use nullish fallback: `arr[i] ?? 0`.
